article.description: Marcus Harris scored 23 points to help San Diego over Loyola Marymount 77-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Harris leads San Diego over Loyola Marymount 77-69
article.linkText: Harris leads San Diego over Loyola Marymount 77-69
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Marcus Harris scored 23 points to help San Diego over Loyola Marymount 77-69 on Saturday. A close game throughout, it was tied at 68 with 2:30 left. Harris scored on a put-back, and then after LMU missed twice, Duda Sanadze hit a jumper. LMU's Adom Jacko made 1 of 2 from the line, but Harris responded with another jump shot to make it 72-69. The Lions missed again next time down, and resorted to fouling. Jito Kok made four straight, then Harris made 1 of 2, to ice it. Kok finished with 17 points for San Diego (7-14, 2-8 West Coast). Sanadze came off the bench for 12. The Toreros hit on 10 of 20 beyond the arc led by Harris, who was good on 4 of 8. Jacko paced Loyola Marymount (10-12, 3-8) with 20 points, and Brandon Brown added 13.
